						<summary>

						<p>On a pillar in the museum with in the compound of the Sōmēśvara temple. First pillar Museum No. 81.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">11th century A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>This record though engraved on the other (fourth) face of No. 191 has not been noticed in the Annual Report for the year 1961-62.</p>						

						<p>The top and bottom portion of the record are damaged and the information there in are lost. The extant portion carries a sting of epithets of <hi rend="italic">mahāmaṇḍaḷēśvara</hi> Kāṁbaya. Mentions (Cheru) Bemarasa of Koḷḷipāka.</p>						

						<p>On paleographical grounds the record can be ascribed to the same period as in No. 191.</p>						

						</summary>
